article.headline: Morehead State 82, Jacksonville St. 68
article.story: MOREHEAD, Ky. (AP) -- Ricky Minard scored 36 points to lead Morehead State to an 82-68 win over Jacksonville State in the first round of the Ohio Valley Conference tournament Tuesday night. Minard was 9-of-17 from the field and 16-of-22 from the line, where the Eagles (16-12) made 30 of 42 shots. Chad McKnight added 15 points and Ramon Kelly 13. Jacksonville State hit all 11 of its free throws but was whistled for 29 fouls to 13 for the Eagles. Walker D. Russell was 9-of-9 from the line and 11-of-18 from the field for 32 points and also had 10 assists. Trent Eager scored 10 points for the Gamecocks. Morehead State advances to play Murray State, a 92-75 winner over Tennessee Tech in another first-round game Tuesday, in the semifinals Friday of the OVC tournament at Nashville, Tenn. The Eagles led 37-30 at halftime. Jacksonville State pulled to within three points at 54-51 with 11:51 left in the game before Morehead State went on a 12-0 run to put the game away.
